The paper deals with anisotropic Voronoi diagrams, which are a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses the practical utility of the analysis, which suggests that it may be relevant to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The fact that the anisotropic Voronoi diagrams have embedded triangulations as duals suggests that the paper may also be relevant to computational geometry and topology (cs.GR). The paper proposes conditions that can be efficiently evaluated, which suggests that it may be relevant to numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper discusses the well-behaved-ness of the diagrams, which suggests that it may be relevant to control systems and optimization (cs.SY).
